---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 192
  - Title: The Cloud of Unknowing
    Location: XLIV
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Humility=Contrition
  - 66
---
He may make sorrow earnestly that knoweth and feeleth not only what he
is, but that he is. And whoso felt never this sorrow, let him make
sorrow; for he hath never yet felt perfect sorrow.
